        <h2 class="font-montserrat font-bold text-2xl md:text-3xl text-[#1e3a5f] mb-6">Types of Boat Finance Available</h2>
        <h3 class="font-montserrat font-semibold text-xl text-[#0d4d3e] mt-8 mb-4">Secured Boat Loan</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light leading-relaxed mb-4">The most common option. The boat (and sometimes the motor and trailer) acts as security for the loan. Rates are lower because the lender has an asset to recover if you default. Requires the boat to be registered and comprehensively insured. Most lenders have minimum loan amounts of $10,000-$20,000 for secured marine finance. Newer boats (under 5-10 years old) qualify for the best secured rates.</p>
        <h3 class="font-montserrat font-semibold text-xl text-[#0d4d3e] mt-8 mb-4">Unsecured Personal Loan for Boats</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light leading-relaxed mb-4">An unsecured personal loan can be used to purchase any boat regardless of age, type, or condition. No asset is attached to the loan. Rates are higher than secured options (typically 7-12% p.a. for good credit) but there are no restrictions on vessel age, no mandatory insurance requirement from the lender, and no PPSR registration. Useful for older boats, unusual vessels, or smaller purchases under $10,000.</p>
        <h3 class="font-montserrat font-semibold text-xl text-[#0d4d3e] mt-8 mb-4">Chattel Mortgage for Commercial Marine</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light leading-relaxed mb-4">If the boat is used predominantly for business purposes — such as commercial fishing, charter operations, diving tours, or marine construction — a chattel mortgage allows you to claim GST on the purchase, deduct interest as a business expense, and depreciate the vessel. This can significantly reduce the effective cost of the boat. Nik Finance has access to commercial marine finance lenders who specialise in business vessel purchases.</p>
        <h3 class="font-montserrat font-semibold text-xl text-[#0d4d3e] mt-8 mb-4">Boat Dealer Finance</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light leading-relaxed mb-4">Many marine dealers offer their own finance, arranged through a finance provider they have a relationship with. Dealer finance can be convenient but rates are often higher than what you could arrange independently through a broker. Just like with car finance, getting pre-approved through Nik Finance before visiting a dealer gives you a rate benchmark and negotiating power.</p>
        </section>
