          <ul class="space-y-3 my-6">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3"><svg class="w-5 h-5 text-[#10b981] mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg><span class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light">Get pre-approved before visiting dealers or boat shows — avoid being pressured into expensive dealer finance on the spot</span></li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3"><svg class="w-5 h-5 text-[#10b981] mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg><span class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light">Compare the comparison rate, not just the headline rate — fees can add significantly to the total cost of a boat loan</span></li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3"><svg class="w-5 h-5 text-[#10b981] mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg><span class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light">Consider the total cost of boat ownership before committing — mooring or marina berth fees, insurance, registration, maintenance, antifouling, fuel, and storage can easily add $3,000-$10,000+ per year on top of loan repayments</span></li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3"><svg class="w-5 h-5 text-[#10b981] mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg><span class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light">Choose the shortest loan term you can comfortably afford — boats depreciate faster than cars, so a longer term increases negative equity risk</span></li>
